    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="har.00049.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><hi rend="underline">Camden NJ</hi><ptr target="har.00049_n1"
                        /></name>
                    <date when="1883-10-14" rend="right"><hi rend="underline">Oct: 14
                        '83</hi></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            
            <p><choice>
                    <abbr>Rec'd</abbr>
                    <expan>Received</expan>
                </choice> your letter<ptr target="har.00049_n2"/>&#8212;I send three photo's by same
                mail with this&#8212;is the profile one something like what you want?&#8212;I don't
                know but I have already sent you the front face with hand up, as I designed one for
                you&#8212;but as I am not certain I send this&#8212;I have just returned from two
                weeks down along the Jersey sea beach, &#38; am well as usual&#8212;always glad to
                hear from you&#8212;hope we shall be together again one of these days&#8212;give my
                best love to Mrs. <choice> 
                        <abbr>F</abbr>
                        <expan>Fairchild</expan>
                    </choice><!-- Miller has an F in his transcription & has an annotation on who "Mrs. Fairchild" is, but in the actual letter it looks like an "L".  -->
                and to <choice>
                    <abbr>B.O'R</abbr><expan>Boyle O'Reilly</expan></choice><ptr target="har.00049_n3"/>&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">W W</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="har.00049.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
